    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-01-12T12:41:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-01-12T12:41:00-05:00" n="709"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d709">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 165.102/793</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in the Netherlands</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_VDH1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Van Dyke</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">The Hague</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-01-12T18:00:00+00:19">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 12, 1916, 6 p. m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 8.20 p. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>479. For Department of Commerce.</p>
                <p>86. Some signs of loosening dyestuffs if I can assure shippers of British
                    noninterference. Try to have discretion given British authorities here to sign
                    permits. Hurry before German end closes again. </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_TEW1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Thompson</hi>
                        </persName>,</signed>
                    <hi rend="italic">Commercial Attaché</hi>
                    <lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_VDH1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Van Dyke</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
